    "narrative": "The Austin Waves roster is primed for a high-efficiency day, anchored by **Kyle Tucker** (85.72), who represents our strongest play due to an ideal combination of a favorable hitter\u2019s park and an exploitable matchup against Sugano. Joining him in the elite tier is **Gunnar Henderson** (79.49), whose score is significantly boosted by a dynamic platoon advantage against Bibee and a prime spot in the two-hole. We are also capitalizing on high-ceiling matchups for **Andy Pages** (75.57) and **Drake Baldwin** (72.00), both of whom benefit from favorable SP skill metrics that elevate their daily output well above their baseline projections.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today involved the exclusion of **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (60.17), who narrowly missed the cut. While he possesses an elite xwOBA of 0.384, the optimizer favored the high-floor versatility of **Marcell Ozuna** (61.71) and the volume of favorable platoon matchups elsewhere in the lineup. We are also monitoring the SB-centric profile of **Brady House** (46.20); despite his potential to capitalize on the opposing pitcher's slow delivery, the high-skill ceiling of the starting infielders kept him on the bench. \n\nCaution is advised regarding the \"Lineup Pending\" status across our entire roster, particularly for **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, who faces the formidable Logan Webb. While **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** holds a respectable 57.07 score due to a dynamic platoon edge, Webb represents the toughest SP hurdle on today\u2019s card. Additionally, while **Josh Lowe** (70.08) and **Nolan Schanuel** (63.36) are in prime spots against the soft-tossing Waldron, any late-breaking weather shifts could compress their projected scoring. We will continue to monitor the statuses of **Liam Hicks**, **Jacob Wilson**, **Miguel Vargas**, **Heliot Ramos**, **Jackson Merrill**, **Jordan Westburg**, **Jorge Polanco**, **Nasim Nunez**, **Josh Jung**, and **Coby Mayo** as lineups finalize to ensure our efficiency thresholds hold.",
